## Parte 6 — Firestore: estructura de colecciones

Para tus 3 usos (informes, historial CSV, usuarios):
```
firestore/
├── users/
│   └── {uid}/
│       ├── email, nombre, rol
│       └── createdAt
│
├── informes/
│   └── {informeId}/
│       ├── uid (quién lo generó)
│       ├── turno, fecha
│       ├── kpis { totalLlamadas, abandonadas, ... }
│       └── createdAt
│
└── historial_csv/
    └── {entradaId}/
        ├── uid
        ├── archivos [ { nombre, tipo, filas } ]
        └── timestamp
```

### Reglas de Firestore (`firestore.rules`)
```
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    match /users/{uid} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth.uid == uid;
    }

    match /informes/{informeId} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null
                  && resource.data.uid == request.auth.uid;
      allow create: if request.auth != null;
    }

    match /historial_csv/{id} {
      allow read, write: if request.auth != null
                         && resource.data.uid == request.auth.uid;
    }
  }
}
```

